<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Tobyl,<br>
Just wanted to correct something you stated..<br>
<br>
Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 yes its very possible to evade and still have agro.<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
From a Rogues stand point, with our Evade skill, this is not true. It's coded that when we have a successful evade, that we drop between the 2nd and 3rd position on the hate list or 500 points, which ever is greater. Which means that from Verants own words, there should never be a successful-failed evade. (Assuming that the mob isn't rooted, or proximity agro, etc) <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
With all due respect, this is nonsense.  Evade seems to reduce aggro/hate--not change one's position in the hate list directly.  Two things are wrong with your statement:<br>
<br>
1. A successful evade can still have you being hit.  You stated this was not true but it clearly is.  I have evaded successfully on a non-rooted mob at max melee range and not switched auto-attack back on or backstabbed and still had aggro; and<br>
<br>
2. Evading even when you don't have aggro seems to reduce your likelihood of later getting aggro.  That being said, depending on the monster, I tend to only evade when I need to rather than in a more preventitive fashion.<br>
<br>
Does evade need to be changed?  Maybe.  It does fail a lot.  I would've like to have seen a rise in the hide cap post-50.  That should allow it to improve.<br>
<br>
What also would've been better was rogue class AAs that make evade cycle faster, work more often, have a more powerful effect when it does work or a combination thereof.  This would be MUCH better than some of the other crap we get like chaotic stab.<br>
<br>
What I'd REALLY like to see though is having your hide skill be able to go up from evading.  I find it ridiculous that this is not the case now (it never has been).  Hide is an awful slow skill to go up (in my experience).  The fact that it can only go up out of combat means i have to mash the key to get it to go up when all my in-combat uses will do nothing for it.  In fact I didn't get to Hide 200 until level 54 (it was 193 at 50).<br>
<br>
Improvements I'd like to see:<br>
<br>
1. Raise the hide cap to 220-250;<br>
2. Give class AAs to decrease cycle time (and maybe make it work more and/or have a larger effect);<br>
3. Allow hide to go up from in-combat use.<br>
<br>
I don't think thats too unreasonable and that would make me very happy.<br>
